            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-11-26 11:50:38" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a feeling of apprehension or distress in view of possible danger or misfortune</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>anxiety</Gloss>
                <Gloss>worry</Gloss>
                <Gloss>anxious concern</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>For μέριμνα as part of an idiom in {S:06000500700006}, see {D:25.250}.|The term μέριμνα may refer to either unnecessary worry or legitimate concern. The equivalent of ‘worry’ may be expressed in some languages in an idiomatic manner, for example, ‘to be killed by one’s mind’ or ‘to be pained by thinking.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
